cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

This paper deals with a problem in computer vision, specifically in visual recognition tasks, where a classifier trained on a source dataset performs poorly on a target dataset due to domain shifts. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a solution that involves learning new data representations and preserving discriminative information, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses optimal transport to measure discrepancy, which could place it in cs.CL (Computation and Language) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
